Javascript is a high level, interpreted programming language
- by intepreted, it means that you execute without having to run it in a compiler. 
- is a multi-paradigm: you can write object oriented code, functionial. 
- Runs on the client as well as on the server. 
- s
Why learn javascript?
- It is the programming language of the browser
- Build interactive user interfaces with frameworks like React
- Used in building very fast server side and fullstack applications
-Used in mobile development.
Used in desktop application development. 
- 

JAVASCRIPT VARIABLES
- Three ways to declare variables: var,let, const
- var is globally scoped
- let and const have block scope


